                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.57/57: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-02T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 2, 1940—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 2—2:39 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2534. From Schoenfeld. Your 2081, July 29, 7 p.m. The Norwegian Foreign Minister
                    received me this afternoon.</p>
                <p>Professor Koht, obviously having in mind his inquiry of Ambassador Kennedy on
                    July 1st (reference telegram No. 1921, July 1, midnight, final paragraph),
                    expressed appreciation of the designation of a representative near the
                    Government of Norway now established in England. [Schoenfeld.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
